Call of Cthulhu

Price InfoHistoryStatsRegions
WaitCollectIgnore
Shop SelectionAll stores selected
Select:allmarkedinversenone
Marked stores are currently selling this game

Price OverviewPrice Detail

Price Overview chart shows development of price over time
  • How often is this game on sale? Are deals getting better?
  • How quickly did it reach current historical low?
  • Is historical low being repeated?
  • Is the regular price of the game dropping?
  • Do all stores drop price?
Price Detail chart shows a per-store view of price history
  • When and how good deals did a store have?
  • Do all stores have deals at the same time?
  • How much prices differ between stores?
  • Are there any differences between sale frequency?
\r\n

Cut OverviewSavings

Cut Overview chart shows development of price cuts over time
  • How often is this game on sale? What is the deals cut?
  • How often are deals repeated?
  • How quickly did price cuts reached current level?
Savings chart shows absolute value of price cut
If regular price drops, same price cut won't mean same savings
\r\n

Sales DistributionSales Duration

Sales distribution chart can tell you when there usually is a sale during a year
  • When are deals more frequent?
  • Are deals with higher cut more frequent during certain time of year?
Note that frequency is aggregate over all historical data and all selected stores
Sales duration chart may tell you how long a sale usually lasts
  • Do deals with smaller cut last longer? By how much?
  • What is a median duration of a sale?
  • How many times was a game on sale with a price cut?
Note that frequency is aggregate over all historical data and all selected stores

Plunge into Cyanide Studio's Call of Cthulhu, the official Cthulhu videogame inspired by Chaosium's classic pen and paper RPG. Uncover the chilling mysteries of this RPG-investigation game, descending deep into a world of cosmic horrors, creeping madness, and shrouded Old Gods within Lovecraft's iconic universe.\r\rThe Cthulhu Mythos has been fascinating audiences for generations, growing to become one of the largest shared universes ever envisioned and giving birth to countless stories, novels, movies, tabletop and videogames since the original publication of H.P. Lovecraft's The Call of Cthulhu. Adaptions and references have formed a widespread legacy stretching back to the very beginning of the 20th century, latching on to the key fear of the human psyche: that of the unknown. Now, Call of Cthulhu will bring the mythos to life like never before, on PlayStation 4, Xbox One and PC.\r\rIn this world, nothing is as it seems. Sanity is an irregular bedfellow, all too often replaced by the whisperings in the dark. Strange creatures, weird science, and shadowy cults dominate the Cthulhu Mythos, intent on realizing their mad schemes to bring about the end of everything. Your mind will suffer -- balancing a razor-thin line between sanity and madness, your senses will be disrupted until you question the reality of everything around you. Trust no one. Creeping shadows hide lurking figures... and all the while, the Great Dreamer prepares for his awakening.
— Metacritic.com
